original_definition: 'data access log' means a timestamped record of data items accessed that includes at least the identification of the final customer or the eligible party accessing the data and, if applicable, the identification of the permission used to access the data;
generated_definition: 'data access log' means a record of all data accessed by users, kept up to date and available to final customers through an online or other appropriate interface, free of charge and without unnecessary delay, upon request.
